## M15b.1 per GPT-5.5 post-impl review entry 41: bare `print` as
## a value (not as a call) is NOT whitelisted. Only the direct
## call shape `print(...)` is special-cased in `synthCall`'s
## unknown-callee branch. Treating bare `print` as a flowable
## value would be the same fake-surface anti-pattern the
## leaf-position unbound check closes for everything else.

sub main()
  x = print
  x(42)
